headline: TDG Q2 Deep Dive: OEM Headwinds and Aftermarket Moderation Shape Guidance
summary: Aerospace and defense company TransDigm (NYSE:TDG) missed Wall Street’s revenue expectations in Q2 CY2025, but sales rose 9.3% year on year to $2.24 billion. The company’s full-year revenue guidance of $8.79 billion at the midpoint came in 0.9% below analysts’ estimates. Its non-GAAP profit of $9.60 per share was 3.1% below analysts’ consensus estimates.
